  <compounddef id="GOSUB" kind="page">
    <compoundname>GOSUB</compoundname>
    <title>GOSUB Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">GOSUB<sp/>numeric-constant</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Transfers control to the line with the given <bold>constant line number</bold>, saving the return address so that execution can continue at the statement <bold>after</bold> the <computeroutput>GOSUB</computeroutput> when a matching <computeroutput>RETURN</computeroutput> is encountered.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="remark"><para><bold>Deprecated / discouraged.</bold> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>Use structured procedures instead: </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>define with <computeroutput>DEF PROCname(...) ... ENDPROC</computeroutput> and call with <computeroutput>PROCname(...)</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para><computeroutput>GOSUB</computeroutput> is retained for compatibility with legacy, line-numbered code.</para>
</simplesect>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The target must be a <bold>numeric constant</bold> (no expressions or variables).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The target line must exist <bold>within the current program</bold>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Each <computeroutput>GOSUB</computeroutput> must eventually reach a <computeroutput>RETURN</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Example: simple subroutine (line numbers permitted)</heading>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">10<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Start&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">20<sp/>GOSUB<sp/>1000</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">30<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Back<sp/>from<sp/>subroutine&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">40<sp/>END</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">1000<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Inside<sp/>subroutine&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">1010<sp/>RETURN</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Example: using variables with a subroutine</heading>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">10<sp/>N<sp/>=<sp/>3</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">20<sp/>GOSUB<sp/>2000</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">30<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Done&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">40<sp/>END</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">2000<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Counting...&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">2010<sp/>FOR<sp/>I<sp/>=<sp/>1<sp/>TO<sp/>N</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">2020<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>I</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">2030<sp/>NEXT</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">2040<sp/>RETURN</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Notes</heading>
</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>GOSUB</computeroutput> does not support arguments. Share data via variables; prefer <computeroutput>PROC</computeroutput> parameters in new code.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Jumping to a line that does not contain the intended subroutine body will execute whatever is there until a <computeroutput>RETURN</computeroutput> is hit.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Modern Retro Rocket BASIC code should prefer **<computeroutput>DEF PROC</computeroutput> / <computeroutput>PROC</computeroutput>** for clarity and maintainability.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
